Delicious fast casual Mediterranean food bursting with flavor, better than Cava! While Cava is good, Roti has higher quality and better ingredients with more manageable portions. The turmeric rice is very flavorful and love to the fire roasted veggies. It's nice to not have to choose my protein between falafel or veggies. I can get both at Roti with a scoop of veggies without getting skimped on the falafel. At Cava, I would always have to choose between the two or get skimped on something! The fluffy cous cous and crispy falafel are quite tasty. All the sides and hummus, garlic lemon and spicy roasted red pepper dressings are flavorful. It's hard to go wrong!  The chocolate chip cookies are a hit/miss depending on the location and time of day. If you can catch a freshly baked cookie out of the oven, they are hands-down the best cookies in DC with a a crispy shell and soft and goey inside. However if they've been packaged for hours, they taste stale and need to warm them up - not a fan. These sadly were stale!  Sad to see many Roti locations temporarily closed including the one in my area in Vienna. Please reopen them soon! Worth a trip into DC for some Roti!

Recently: first time visiting this location which is the closest to my residence. The service was...sufficient I guess, but the demeanor to go along with it, not so much. I guess my server was so focused on rushing to provide my order so that she could be done cleaning before closing that she didn't pay full attention to what I wanted to order. So much so, despite me responding "No" when she thought she was stating what I wanted, I still had to repeat myself twice before she looked at me to pay attention. I was distinctly asking for flatbread then pizza and told her not a wrap & that I had not said pita. After all of that, I paid for my order and was still at the register she began to interact with who turned out to be the last customer who entered after me even though she wasn't creating his order. I noticed that she exhibited differential treatment telling him "thank you, have a good night". And he exited the restaurant before I did because I had to stop and get napkins. Then a guy came out from the rear and was talking about how the day went, and all of a sudden all became quiet; like somebody 'shushed' him - just before I walked out of the door. Still, I heard not even 'good night'.  As far as my order: the lamb meatballs were pretty stiff and a little dry. My bowl was overall bland in flavor, maybe because I didn't ask for olives since I didn't see them out.... or due to the energy of the person who created my order? It so happens I visited another Roti a few days prior and the overall experience including food taste was like night and day between locations.
